/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.3/claude/review-01-messy-ts-app.json:  "response": "## Verdict: 2 block · 11 warn · 9 ignore\n\nCategorisation logic: **block** if a finding is either high-severity *or* a real defect that ships broken behaviour an agent can't recover from. **Warn** for medium-severity findings — agent_risk in the 0.5–0.6 band means future edits are likely to compound the mess, but nothing is outright wrong today. **Ignore** for low-severity stylistic / hygiene findings that don't shift the risk profile of this PR.\n\n### Block merge (2)\n\n| ID | Charge | sev / agent_risk | Why block |\n|----|--------|------------------|-----------|\n| crime_00001 | God Function (`generateInvoice`, 204 lines, 3.4× threshold) | **high** / 0.63 | Only `high` finding in the report. 204-line domain function ships unreviewable code; any subsequent agent edit will miss interactions. Should be split before this lands. |\n| crime_00006 | Test That Proves Nothing (`\"renders the enterprise plan\"`, 0 expects) | medium 0.45 / 0.46 | Scores are mid, but this test is the named coverage for the God Function above — it actively creates false confidence. A no-op test in the same PR as the function it claims to cover is a defect, not a smell. Delete or assert. |\n\n### Warn (11)\n\nAll medium severity, agent_risk clustered 0.50–0.61. Author should address or explicitly acknowledge before merge, but none independently breaks the build:\n\n| ID | Charge | sev / agent_risk | Note |\n|----|--------|------------------|------|\n| crime_00002 | Missing Agent Context | 0.6 / 0.61 | High agent_risk by construction — repo ships zero agent instructions. Fixable in one file. |\n| crime_00004 | Temporal Recklessness (`billing.ts`, 7 calls) | 0.6 / 0.53 | Domain code reading wall clock; couples future tests to time. |\n| crime_00005 | Temporal Recklessness (`date.ts`, 5 calls) | 0.6 / 0.61 | Same pattern, test_gap=1 pushes agent_risk higher. |\n| crime_00007 | String Sprinkle