/claude/context-10-clean-typed.json:7:  \\\"response\\\": \\\"**No findings on `src/billing.ts`.**\\\\n\\\\n- **Risk level:** `none` (0 high / 0 medium / 0 low)\\\\n- **likely_tests:** `src/billing.test.ts`\\\\n- **agent_guidance:** none — *\\\\\\\"no findings on this file and no deterministic related files\\\\\\\"*\\\\n- **related_files:** none — no IA related-files signal, no shared domain tokens, no domain-prefix filenames, no same-directory siblings\\\\n\\\\n**Why this module is low risk to edit:**\\\\n\\\\n1. **Clean detector sweep.** No structural, dependency, duplication, testability, or churn findings — none of the v0 detectors fired, so there's no known God Function, layer violation, hidden side effect, or churn hotspot to step on.\\\\n2. **Co-located test exists.** `src/billing.test.ts` is the deterministic sibling test path, so changes have a ready safety net — the `test_gap` score on this file is implicitly low.\\\\n3. **Isolated neighbourhood.** No related files via imports or domain tokens means the blast radius is contained to this file plus its test — edits won't cascade into other modules that share state or naming.\\\\n4. **No agent_risk signals.** No misleading names, no multiple sources of truth, no hidden side effects flagged — an agent editing this file isn't walking into a trap the linter would miss.\\\\n\\\\nNet: edit freely, run `src/billing.test.ts`, ship.\\\",\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_5\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"`crimes context src/Card.tsx` currently surfaces only `accessible_interaction_risk`, but the source also contains the fixture’s two intended frontend risks: inline hex styles and fixed pixel width.\\n\\nProposed refactor:\\n\\n```tsx\\ntype CardProps = {\\n  children: React.ReactNode;\\n  onActivate?: () => void;\\n};\\n\\nconst cardClassName = \\\"w-full max-w-3xl bg-brand-accent text-foreground\\\";\\n\\nexport function Card({ children, onA