/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.5/claude/plan-01-messy-ts-app.json:  "response": "# Triage plan — top 10 findings (ordered by agent_risk)\n\nNote: `crimes verdict --format json` output wasn't included, so this ranks by `agent_risk` (per the PRD's \"aggregate risk, not severity alone\" rule). The top 10 cleanly map to four of the five categories — no top-10 finding has churn > 0, so the **git-history** bucket is empty here.\n\n## Structural\n\n| # | Finding | agent_risk | Response | Why |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `crime_00001` God Function `generateInvoice` (`src/billing.ts:50-253`) | 0.63 | **Fix now** | High sev + 0.95 conf. Unblocks safe edits to billing; extracting helpers also makes #9 trivial. |\n| 3 | `crime_00005` Temporal Recklessness (`src/date.ts:4-22`) | 0.61 | **Fix now** | Small module, 5 call sites — cheapest place to introduce a `now()` abstraction that #9 can reuse. |\n| 9 | `crime_00004` Temporal Recklessness (`src/billing.ts`, 7 sites) | 0.53 | **Defer** | Land with #1 — clock injection naturally falls out of the `generateInvoice` extraction. |\n| 10 | `crime_00008` False Identity `calculateRefundPreview` | 0.52 | **Fix now** | Rename-or-split is a minutes-long change with outsized clarity payoff; pair with #11 (logic-in-comments on same function). |\n\n## IA (information architecture)\n\n| # | Finding | agent_risk | Response | Why |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 2 | `crime_00002` Missing Agent Context | 0.61 | **Fix now** | Cheapest high-leverage fix in the report. An AGENTS.md/CLAUDE.md compounds across every future agent edit. |\n| 4 | `crime_00007` String Sprinkles `\"enterprise\"` (4 files) | 0.60 | **Fix now** | Centralise before a 5th copy lands; touches files in #5 and #6 so do it before they shift. |\n| 5 | `crime_00009` Concept Alias Drift (tenant/account/org/team/workspace) | 0.58 | **Defer** | Real cost is a naming decision, not a refactor. Park until product picks the canonical term; don't let an agent guess. |\n\n## Frontend\n\n| # | Finding | agent_risk | Response | Why |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 6 | `crime_00012` Duplicated Navigation Source (`/settings/billing`) | 0.57 | **Fix now** | Bundle with #8 — same destination, same PR, single nav-canonicalisation. |\n| 8 | `crime_00014` Route Metadata Drift (`/settings/billing`) | 0.56 | **Fix now** | Same destination as #6; aligning route/title/nav labels is one diff, not two. |\n\n## Duplication\n\nThe duplication category in the top 10 is covered by the IA findings above — `String Sprinkles` (#4) and `Duplicated Navigation Source` (#6) are the duplication signals; the dedicated `duplicate_block` / `near_duplicate_function` detectors didn't fire on this fixture.\n\n## (Slot 7) — judgement call\n\n| # | Finding | agent_risk | Response | Why |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 7 | `crime_00013` Unfinished Business (`src/todo.ts`, 424/1k LOC) | 0.57 | **Ignore** | The file is named `todo.ts` and exists to demo this detector — treat as fixture, suppress in `.crimes/ignore`. If this were prod code: **fix now**. |\n\n---\n\n## Recommended PR sequencing\n\n1. **PR A — agent context** (#2): drop in `AGENTS.md`. Minutes.\n2. **PR B — billing cleanup** (#1 + #4 + #8 + #10 + #11): split `generateInvoice`, inject clock, rename `calculateRefundPreview`, encode the comment rule. One coherent refactor of `src/billing.ts`.\n3. **PR C — clock module** (#3): land `src/date.ts` clock abstraction first if PR B will consume it; otherwise fold in.\n4. **PR D — enterprise constant** (#4 / `crime_00007`): one-line constant, four import sites.\n5. **PR E — billing route alignment** (#6 + #8): collapse nav sources, align route metadata for `/settings/billing`.\n6. **Backlog**: #5 (alias drift — needs product call), `crime_00010` God File (resolves naturally after PR B), orphaned routes (`crime_00021-23` — need product call: in-flight or dead?).",
/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.5/claude/refactor-08-architecture.json:  "response": "## Layer violation (crime_00002) — domain → presentation\n\n`src/domain/billing.ts` imports `src/presentation/invoice-view.ts`, violating `domain cannotImport presentation`.\n\n**Break this import.** The domain layer must not know how an invoice renders. Two options, in order of preference:\n\n1. **Invert via an interface.** Define a port in `src/domain/` (e.g. `InvoiceRenderer` or just the data shape the domain needs to *return*). Have the presentation file implement/consume it, and have `src/application/billing-flow.ts` wire the concrete renderer in. The domain ends up importing nothing from presentation.\n2. **Extract a shared type.** If the import was only for a type (e.g. `InvoiceView`), pull that type into a neutral module — `src/domain/types.ts` or a shared module both layers can read — and convert the surviving edge to `import type` so it has no runtime weight.\n\nEither fix also helps with **crime_00001** (the 3-file cycle `application → domain → presentation → application`): removing the domain→presentation runtime edge collapses the ring.\n\n## Deep import (crime_00003) — past a package boundary\n\n`src/application/billing-flow.ts` imports `some-pkg/dist/internal/private/helper.js`.\n\n**Redirect this import.** Three steps:\n\n1. Switch to the package's documented entry: `import { helper } from 'some-pkg'`.\n2. If `helper` isn't re-exported, contain the damage: create one local adapter (`src/infrastructure/some-pkg-adapter.ts`) that is the *only* file reaching into the deep path, and have `billing-flow.ts` consume the adapter. This means a future upstream rename touches one file, not many.\n3. File an upstream issue requesting a public export, so the adapter can eventually be deleted.\n\nThe adapter belongs in **infrastructure**, not application — keeps the application layer free of vendor internals.\n\n## How the two differ in agent risk\n\n| | layer_violation (0.63) | deep_import (0.52) |\n|---|---|---|\n| **What it lies about** | The folder name. An agent reading `src/domain/` assumes domain rules apply (pure, no UI), but a presentation import means that assumption is silently false. Edits made under the wrong mental model land wrong. | A version pin. The import path *looks* fine syntactically; the breakage is deferred to whenever someone runs `pnpm up`. The current behavior is correct. |\n| **When it bites** | Now, on every edit — every refactor in `billing.ts` has to account for an invisible coupling to a view. | Later, on upgrade — and the failure mode (missing file, changed shape) is loud, not subtle. |\n| **Why the score is higher for layer_violation** | It corrupts the *organizing convention* of the codebase. Agents and humans both navigate by layer; a violated layer makes the map wrong. | The deep path is itself a self-warning — `dist/internal/private/` is hard to miss. The risk is real but the *signal* is clear. |\n\nNet: layer violations are worse for agent risk because they degrade the codebase's own labels; deep imports are worse for *supply-chain* risk but easier for a careful reader to flag at a glance.",
/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.15/claude/refactor-02-component-shape.json:  "response": "## Finding\n\n`crime_00052` — `duplicate_component_shape`, confidence 0.70, agent_risk 0.57. A `<div>` subtree appears in 4 files with the same structural shape.\n\n## Files that would change\n\nThe shared subtree is the **form action bar** (Cancel link + primary submit button) at the bottom of each invoice form:\n\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx:142-150` (`Create Invoice`)\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx:152-160` (`Edit Invoice`)\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx:101-109`\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx:112-120`\n\nBoth starter and final variants would adopt the new component. (`final-example` and `starter-example` are separate Next.js apps in the fixture — each gets its own copy of the shared component unless the two apps share a package, which they don't here.)\n\nNew file per app:\n\n- `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx`\n- `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx`\n\n## Proposed shared component\n\n```tsx\n// app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx\nimport Link from 'next/link';\nimport { Button } from '@/app/ui/button';\nimport type { ReactNode } from 'react';\n\ntype FormActionsProps = {\n  cancelHref: string;\n  submitLabel: ReactNode;     // \"Create Invoice\" | \"Edit Invoice\" | …\n  cancelLabel?: ReactNode;    // default: \"Cancel\"\n  submitDisabled?: boolean;\n  className?: string;         // override the wrapper utility classes\n  children?: ReactNode;       // optional slot: extra actions rendered BEFORE Cancel\n};\n\nexport function FormActions({\n  cancelHref,\n  submitLabel,\n  cancelLabel = 'Cancel',\n  submitDisabled,\n  className = 'mt-6 flex justify-end gap-4',\n  children,\n}: FormActionsProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className={className}>\n      {children}\n      <Link\n        href={cancelHref}\n        className=\"flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-gray-100 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 transition-colors hover:bg-gray-200\"\n      >\n        {cancelLabel}\n      </Link>\n      <Button type=\"submit\" disabled={submitDisabled}>\n        {submitLabel}\n      </Button>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Public API\n\n**Props**\n| Prop | Type | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `cancelHref` | `string` | Required. Where Cancel routes (`/dashboard/invoices` in both call sites today). |\n| `submitLabel` | `ReactNode` | Required. The varying bit — `\"Create Invoice\"` vs `\"Edit Invoice\"`. |\n| `cancelLabel` | `ReactNode` | Optional, defaults to `\"Cancel\"`. Lets future forms localize. |\n| `submitDisabled` | `boolean` | Optional. Lets callers wire `useFormStatus().pending` without re-templating. |\n| `className` | `string` | Optional escape hatch for the wrapper utilities. |\n\n**Slots**\n- `children` — rendered **before** Cancel, for forms that grow a third action (e.g. a \"Save draft\" or \"Delete\" button). Keep it as a single optional slot rather than named `before`/`after` props until a second use case appears.\n\n### Call-site change (representative)\n\n```tsx\n// create-form.tsx — replaces lines 142–150\n<FormActions cancelHref=\"/dashboard/invoices\" submitLabel=\"Create Invoice\" />\n\n// edit-form.tsx — replaces lines 152–160\n<FormActions cancelHref=\"/dashboard/invoices\" submitLabel=\"Edit Invoice\" />\n```\n\n### Notes\n\n- This is a JSX-shape consolidation, not a behavior change — the existing `<form>`, fieldset, and `aria-live` region around it stay put.\n- `final-example` and `starter-example` are separate apps; each needs its own `FormActions` file unless you also introduce a shared package. The shape (props + slot) is identical across both copies, so future drift between them will surface as a `duplicate_component_shape` finding on the new file too — that's the desired signal.\n- Related but **not** addressed by this component: `crime_00053`/`crime_00054` (status string checks scattered across forms + `status.tsx`) and `crime_00051` (`\"status\"` literal repeated in 5 files). Those want a policy module (`invoiceStatus.ts`), not a component.",
