/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.5/claude/refactor-02-component-shape.json:  "response": "## Finding\n\n`crime_00083` — `duplicate_component_shape` — flags a `<div>` subtree repeated across **4 invoice form files**. Confirmed by reading the source: it's the form-actions footer at the bottom of every invoice form. A Cancel link back to `/dashboard/invoices` plus a submit `<Button>` whose only varying text is `Create Invoice` vs `Edit Invoice`.\n\n## Files that would change\n\n1. `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx` (lines 142–150)\n2. `dashboard/final-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx` (lines 152–160)\n3. `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/create-form.tsx` (lines 101–109)\n4. `dashboard/starter-example/app/ui/invoices/edit-form.tsx` (lines 112–120)\n\nPlus one new file per fixture: `dashboard/<example>/app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx`.\n\n## Shared component\n\n```tsx\n// app/ui/invoices/form-actions.tsx\nimport Link from 'next/link';\nimport { ReactNode } from 'react';\nimport { Button } from '@/app/ui/button';\n\ntype FormActionsProps = {\n  submitLabel: ReactNode;        // \"Create Invoice\" | \"Edit Invoice\" | …\n  cancelHref?: string;           // defaults to \"/dashboard/invoices\"\n  cancelLabel?: ReactNode;       // defaults to \"Cancel\"\n  submitDisabled?: boolean;      // optional, for pending states\n};\n\nexport function FormActions({\n  submitLabel,\n  cancelHref = '/dashboard/invoices',\n  cancelLabel = 'Cancel',\n  submitDisabled,\n}: FormActionsProps) {\n  return (\n    <div className=\"mt-6 flex justify-end gap-4\">\n      <Link\n        href={cancelHref}\n        className=\"flex h-10 items-center rounded-lg bg-gray-100 px-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 transition-colors hover:bg-gray-200\"\n      >\n        {cancelLabel}\n      </Link>\n      <Button type=\"submit\" disabled={submitDisabled}>\n        {submitLabel}\n      </Button>\n    </div>\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### Public API\n\n**Props**\n- `submitLabel: ReactNode` — required; the only thing that actually varies today (`\"Create Invoice\"`, `\"Edit Invoice\"`).\n- `cancelHref?: string` — defaults to `/dashboard/invoices`; lets future forms reuse this without forking when they live elsewhere.\n- `cancelLabel?: ReactNode` — defaults to `\"Cancel\"`; cheap i18n / wording flex.\n- `submitDisabled?: boolean` — optional, anticipates Server Action pending states (`useFormStatus`).\n\n**Slots** — none needed for the four current call sites. I deliberately *did not* expose a `children` / \"extra actions\" slot or render-prop for the button: the four duplicates have identical structure, and adding a slot now would re-open the drift surface the extraction is supposed to close. If a third button later appears (e.g. \"Save as draft\"), add a typed `secondaryAction?: ReactNode` slot then — not pre-emptively.\n\n### Call site after refactor\n\n```tsx\n// create-form.tsx\n<FormActions submitLabel=\"Create Invoice\" />\n\n// edit-form.tsx\n<FormActions submitLabel=\"Edit Invoice\" />\n```\n\n### Notes\n\n- The two fixtures (`final-example`, `starter-example`) are independent Next.js tutorial copies, so the component must be duplicated **once per fixture** — you can't share across them without restructuring the fixture. That's 2 new files, 4 edited files.\n- This finding is `medium` / confidence `0.7` for a reason: the subtree is small (~8 lines). The reason to extract isn't line count, it's that the related findings `crime_00084` and `crime_00085` show the same four files already drifting on the `\"pending\"` / `\"paid\"` status checks. Consolidating the actions row makes the next divergence (e.g. a pending-state spinner on submit) land in one place.",
